Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat. Cut kernels off corn. In a bowl, mix together corn kernels, butter, mayonnaise, sour cream, cotija cheese, chili powder, and lime juice and zest. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Place corn mixture on an 18 x 18-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap(R) Heavy Duty Aluminum Foil. Form a packet, sealing folds well. Grill over high heat for about 25 minutes. Carefully open packet and top with cilantro. Serve with lime wedges.